{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"62f23d6160aabc83","type":"text","text":"a basic income for queer and trans artists based on resale equity\n\nwhat if every time anyone's work in the network was resold, the 15% resale cut goes not to the artist themselves but to an equity fund that is spread equally among all the artists in the network?\n\nthere could be more options than just resell value; the initial sale could also be put into the fund by artists in the network. would that be a choice?\n\n\n\n\n\nbut then what happens to people who come into the network later? would it depend on how long you've been in the network?\n\n\n","x":-375,"y":-280,"width":515,"height":420},
		{"id":"d941391aad2dbaeb","x":-721,"y":-341,"width":250,"height":221,"type":"text","text":"art is for everyone\ni want everyone to have it doesnt have to mean free\n\nfractional ownership is the technical representation of collective ownership\n\n"}
